                    "company": "Eindhoven University of Technology",
                    "description": "Full Professor Intelligent Energy Systems in the Electrical Energy Systems (EES) group of the Eindhoven University of Technology (TUe). Principal scientist in intelligent energy systems research and education. Research focus is on smart grids and, more specifically, the application of intelligent software systems, Artificial Intelligence, in (electrical) energy systems in the broadest sense. These intelligent techniques include distributed systems, cyber-physical systems, complexity science and data science. With the team at EES, we focus on two research lines present in the group: distributed intelligence for power systems control & coordination, and data science & machine learning as applied to energy market trade and power systems operations.",
                    "title": "Full Professor Intelligent Energy Systems",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
