                        }
                    },
                    "company": "Eindhoven University of Technology",
                    "description": "Part time professorship (hoogleraar) in power systems control and coordination. Special focus is on the major challenges faced at the distribution grid level in the energy transition. Unleashing the large potential of prosumer flexibility located in the distribution grids is a key prerequisite for a successful energy transition and to accommodate the related ongoing electrification trend (electrification of transport, industry and heating).\nThis professorship is part of a long-lasting cooperation between TU/e and TNO. At TNO, this professorship falls under the Energy R&D Roadmap \"Towards a Reliable Sustainable Energy System\" and is partly financed from TNO ICT. At TU/e, the professorship is part of the Intelligent Power Grid section of the Electrical Energy Systems group.",
